<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-563-043  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 563 043.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Headway releases &quot;The Little Mac Book.&quot; (Headway ComputerProducts) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Headway Publications Ltd. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Computer industryProduct IntroductionReference Books.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HEADWAY RELEASES &quot;THE LITTLE MAC BOOK&quot; ALDERSHOT, HANTS, ENGLAND, 1990 OCT 8(NB) -- Headway Computer Products has released &quot;The Little Mac Book,&quot; a UKP9-95 soft cover book designed for novice users of the Apple Macintosh.andP;  The110 page book has been released just in time for the Mac Classic, the budgetrange of machines that Apple will launch on October 15.andM;According to the author Robin Williams, a graphic designer and instructor incomputer graphics and desktop publishing, the book is just what users need -not everything-you-need-to-know, but some things users must know to becomefamiliar with and feel enough confidence to begin exploring the Mac's designabilities.andM;The Little Mac Book has an ISBN of 0-938151-21-5 and is available from UKbookshops or direct from Headway.andM;(Steve Gold/19901005/Press andamp; Public Contact: Headway Computer Products - Tel:0252-333575)</TEXT></DOC>